legal Alien Kills Two Children (Ages 9 and 12) Riding Their Bikes On The Sidewalk. \r\n\r\n", "last_comment_created": 1776156035978, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 3, "score_up": 117, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "The Spartanburg County Coroner\u2019s Office and the South Carolina Highway Patrol are investigating.", "large_image": "V9OCH4ttebmwfgj6.png", "title": "DUI driver denied bond, to be placed on ICE detainer after 2 boys hit, killed in Upstate: Officials"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZMQsXmY", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 52, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8557356, "raw_content": "", "author": "luckyshot", "created": 1776131411259, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "www.themidwesterner.news", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZMQsXmY.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://www.themidwesterner.news/2026/04/gretchen-whitmers-corporate-welfare-fund-costs-michigan-taxpayers-nearly-800000-per-job/", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Gretchen Whitmer\u2019s corporate welfare fund costs Michigan taxpayers nearly $800,000 per job.", "last_comment_created": 1776131411259, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 0, "score_up": 52, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "Four years after lawmakers created a Strategic Outreach Attraction Reserve Fund to bribe businesses to create jobs in Michigan, it\u2019s finally paying off. But the cost is eye watering. \u201cHiring to date reflects a cost per new job of about $795,000 based on still-active job-creation incentive awards and recent company reports to the state,\u201d Bridge...", "large_image": "pWS5WxcTL1lRUo0Y.png", "title": "Gretchen Whitmer's corporate welfare fund costs Michigan taxpayers nearly $800,000 per job - The Midwesterner"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZMQsolQ", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 43, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8557444, "raw_content": "I am in my early 30s going back to school to finish my degree in business. Yeah yeah, I know colleges are liberal hell holes, but I am tired of being passed up for promotion. \n\nBut god damn guys. I used to think College professors were using their position to push an agenda. No. I thought maybe they were brainwashed. Also no. As a last resort, I thought maybe they really do hate poor people. Nope nope nope. Not at all. \n\nI am very passionate about small scale manufacturing and finding ways to bring a new wave of decentralized production back to the US. I think that is a huge component of MAGA. When I write essays on how we have an army of young people in this country are desperate to be small scale entrepreneurs, these professors look at me like I have 6 heads. I can show them hard evidence of businesses from around the world that do meaningful production work in basements or garages and try to argue that we should be fostering this kind of market in the US, but they literally can't imagine such a thing. \n\nNot because of dogma. But because they literally can't think. These people are outright NPCs. College is not a liberal brainwashing facility. It is an outright NPC factory. And oh by the way, half of our \"business\" lessons involve ignoring workers input, charging more delivering less, and how to lay people off in order to increase profits. And its all, and I mean ALL, coming from Harvard. Every business school I have looked at sets Harvard as their benchmark. And whatever little pieces that they can't get from harvard, they fill in with Pearson and McGraw Hill. I should know. I was just told that these professors go to week long spa retreats courtesy of these companies. \n\nThese ass holes are nothing but enemies of the state, and its everywhere. ", "author": "Marat1792", "created": 1776134900299, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Floridacus", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "I need to vent a bit - Business School. ", "last_comment_created": 1776148638201, "content": "<p>I am in my early 30s going back to school to finish my degree in business. Yeah yeah, I know colleges are liberal hell holes, but I am tired of being passed up for promotion.</p>\n<p>But god damn guys. I used to think College professors were using their position to push an agenda. No. I thought maybe they were brainwashed. Also no. As a last resort, I thought maybe they really do hate poor people. Nope nope nope. Not at all.</p>\n<p>I am very passionate about small scale manufacturing and finding ways to bring a new wave of decentralized production back to the US. I think that is a huge component of MAGA. When I write essays on how we have an army of young people in this country are desperate to be small scale entrepreneurs, these professors look at me like I have 6 heads. I can show them hard evidence of businesses from around the world that do meaningful production work in basements or garages and try to argue that we should be fostering this kind of market in the US, but they literally can't imagine such a thing.</p>\n<p>Not because of dogma. But because they literally can't think. These people are outright NPCs. College is not a liberal brainwashing facility. It is an outright NPC factory. And oh by the way, half of our &quot;business&quot; lessons involve ignoring workers input, charging more delivering less, and how to lay people off in order to increase profits. And its all, and I mean ALL, coming from Harvard. Every business school I have looked at sets Harvard as their benchmark. And whatever little pieces that they can't get from harvard, they fill in with Pearson and McGraw Hill. I should know. I was just told that these professors go to week long spa retreats courtesy of these companies.</p>\n<p>These ass holes are nothing but enemies of the state, and its everywhere.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 6, "score_up": 43, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZMOcqw7", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 488, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8555753, "raw_content": "", "author": "VanillaCupCake", "created": 1776087336020, "profile_picture": "skHhaQnk6Zfk", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Smurfection", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "media.scored.co", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZMOcqw7.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://media.scored.co/post/Z1uWYb7RWBy4.jpeg", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": fa